The paper focuses on the application of deep learning methods for video classification, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) is a common approach in this field, and the paper specifically evaluates a two-stream CNN pipeline. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also discusses important implementation options that affect the performance of deep nets, such as network architectures and learning parameters, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG). 

The use of motion optical flows in the two-stream CNN pipeline is a technique for capturing temporal information in videos, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM). 

The paper also discusses the fusion of models and prediction methods, which are topics related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), respectively.
